have any right.  and you know it. i'll be okay
column3: it may take time but i'll get past this like so many other things.  i'm resilient like that.  you'll likely stay in that ugliness though
column4: and that's it's own sort of justice i suppose.

column1: sometimes you have to keep looking forward
column2: looking towards the places you want to be instead of fighting to get away from the places you can't bear.  it's a process
column3: but i'm willing to work because it's been so rewarding.  stand in the light whenever you can.  be who you are.  those who mind don't matter and those who matter don't mind and all that jazz.

column1: 142009;instagram;2018-11-30 22:16:48;FALSE;"so this year for me is all about making positive changes not only for myself but for tara as well
column2: and choosing happiness. so i decided to started a new tradition in our household for christmas this year
column3: and instead of a buying chocolate advent calender that tara demolishs in 3 days i have taken 24 of her story books and wrapped them up individually. in the first parcel on the top not only does it have her most favorite book
column4: but the parcel also includes one new pair of pj's and one new christmas tee-shirt. so each night she can open one and we read a story together before bed
column5: and for the 24th of december the book is of course twas the night before christmas. i can't wait!!

column1: 142026;instagram;2018-11-30 22:30:53;FALSE;"my last 3 posts were quite heavy and i feel a bit shy in posting new stuff. it all left me feeling raw and exposed and questioning the necessity of sharing my shadows when you all have your own shadows to deal with in your lives. i am the kind who will rather not talk about my darkness as i don't want to put others down and i know myself capable of finding answers on my own.

i am a real person though. i have lived a real life and i like to be as genuine as possible. that #metoo moment shaped the person that i am today. i learned so much in my healing process... it all is such a beautiful journey and my heart longs to share my stories with you
column2: to contribute in a beneficial way to this lovely canvas that is #humankind. .
to all of you who read those posts
column3: to all of you who liked them or wrote to me
column4: thank you. i hope to contribute in more light ways to your lives and i appreciate your support when i occasionally delve into my shadows. .

column1: some days i feel so buried deep
like i‚Äôm sinking into the ground
with weights tied to my feet
but you told me to keep walking
so even when i don‚Äôt feel like talking - i‚Äôll keep walking
walking though my legs are tired - and my back is weak
i‚Äôll keep pushing my way up through the concrete
because somebody somewhere is out there waiting for me
so i gotta do all that i have to do - to be their very best
to save someone who loves me too - but just doesn‚Äôt know it yet
someone once told me that my heart was a flower
that when i was doubting myself - i could fold my hands and find my power
and when the world turned its back in my direction
i‚Äôd know which way to grow even if i couldn‚Äôt see
my saving grace - the future that stood before me
so whenever i find myself feeling despised
when my heart and soul are
i‚Äôll find a way to look up at the sky - and i will rise
each and every day - outside of the shame of yesterday
i won‚Äôt let love take me out - not today - and not this way
and onto my feet - i‚Äôm rising
out of the depths of depression
to take back what was stolen
my peace of mind - my soul
i will never let go - even when it‚Äôs what some expect of me
i will never suffer under the weight of false tyranny
because i - like a saint in a rise - know which way i‚Äôm going
the river still flowing and with each day that passes - i‚Äôm growing still
and i will keep on rising up out of the grave to defend my will
outside of the hurt i once slept beside
outside of the words that hateful men hide behind
outside of the shame that history put on me
between the l‚Äôs - the g‚Äôs - the b‚Äôs - and the t‚Äôs
and i will claim victory in the face of adversity - the same way that maya  did - and still does
each and every day - we will rise again - and we will redefine
what it means to resist and persist throughout time
the jagged edges of weathered mountains - we will climb
out of the darkness and into the light
we will fight and scratch and claw - until there‚Äôs nothing left to fight at all

we are rising - we are rising - and we will never fall.";;en;;;;;;0;;paralysmic_poetry;The Poetry of Nicholas Jones;;0;False;1;0;0;61;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/0490dd5434362880fdfcb429231dcf62/5D227C9C/t51.2885-15/e35/46107765_332369647575640_5217306111390914448_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"rising: rising (1/14) by nicholas jones

column1: this photo was taken outside of my apartment building in nyc the summer of 2001. my friends were taking me to brunch to congratulate me on the news of my pregnancy with my son.

edgar and i worked in a sales office and realised we had attended the same ballet school in nyc at different times.  he asked me to keep it a secret at work as he didn't want the other guys to know that he had once taken ballet and was gay.  i never told a soul.
some in the office even thought we were dating.  as one of only a handful of women in a male dominated office and industry
column2: edgar was a welcomed relief.  this was well before the #metoo movement.

column3: with a wicked sense of humour. we used to do ballet combinations we remembered from shared teachers in the corridors of skyscrapers before walking in and meeting with clients or cold calling new prospects.

column2: to mums who have struggled with alcohol. to show that being af is not the end but the beginning of getting better. that motherhood/parenthood and being a human is hard. especially for women - that we have traumas

column1: 142546;instagram;2018-12-01 16:17:27;FALSE;"i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.
steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?
abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me
column2: a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

column1: the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.
and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets

column1: 142603;instagram;2018-12-01 17:40:18;FALSE;"i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.
steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?
abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me
column2: a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

column1: the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

column1: 142715;instagram;2018-12-01 20:12:38;FALSE;"muniya was 22 years old a university student when she was drug raped by a very close friend of hers  her friend got a job abroad so he confessed his feelings to her and said am leaving the country i want to settle down come back and take you as my wife muniya rejected him kindly and said i see you as a brother and never had more than a brotherly feeling towards you i'm sorry if i gave you a wrong impression i love you as a family member he didn't take it well and left furious muniya tried calling him several times to appolagize but he didn't respond hours before his departure he calls her and says i have 4 hours left i want to have my last lunch with you and appolagize for the way i left you that day muniya said yes i'd love too he orders everything she loved to her favourite drink not knowing he slipped a pill drug in her drink a while later she felt dizzy and not well so he takes her back to his place and raped her muniya woke up bleeding and in so much pain not knowing what happened to her losing her virginity & being raped she starts losing her mind her male friend left a letter saying i wanted to have a future with you since u said no i got what i wanted from you & goodluck in life.. muniya went histerical and wanted to suicide instantly luckly her friend calls to check up on her she knew from her voice that muniya was not acting normal she goes to muniya and takes her to the hospital to get all the check ups she needs and sat there till she rested in the ward muniya friend told her that she is not in this by her self and no matter what happens as i took this pic of muniya she closes her eyes reliving that moment

column1: as you may have seen from my posts here and on twitter (@monikaproffitt) i have been running around from conference to conference at a pretty fast clip for the better part of 2018. i founded a company
column3: and boot strapped it just like every project or company i've ever made. but because i knew this idea was bigger than anything i'd done before
column4: i needed to learn how to raise outside funding for this company to really grow.

column1: so i built out the business concept
column3: wrote the whitepaper and the summary/ one pager
column5: crafted the branding and the website
column6: and when i lost my volunteer front end designer to a paying job (how can i blame him?)
column7: i taught myself interface design on framer software in an afternoon
column8: and made the first front end mock up of the rise housing platform.

column1: so that i could illustrate what this zillow meets etrade platform could look like.

column2: raising venture capital was something that i had never done
column3: and was confounded by. in the past when i've started a company
column4: i've always just made the thing
column7: grown ancillary lines of business to augment it
column8: and that was that. no distractions. but raising money from outside investors means that you do all of that
column9: while also trying to convince people who move more money before lunch than you've ever seen in your lifetime
column10: that you have a good idea and you are a good bet.
